# Design

## Architecture

- `apps/web` owns the user-facing SPA shell.
- `packages/ui` owns reusable UI primitives.
- `packages/api-client` owns typed `fetch` helpers and error modeling.
- `packages/shared` owns pure helpers and type-safe cross-package utilities.
- `packages/hooks` owns reusable React hooks.
- `packages/theme` owns design tokens and shared CSS variables.
- `packages/config-*` own lint, TypeScript, Tailwind, and test configuration.

## Extension Rules

- Add new features under `apps/web/src/features/<feature-name>`.
- Prefer adding new workspace packages only when code is reused by more than one surface.
- Keep network contracts typed at the boundary by extending `packages/api-client`.
